<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 5:29AM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...PATCHY FOG THIS MORNING...
Surface observations and satellite imagery indicate that patchy
fog, perhaps locally dense, has developed across Zapata, Jim
Hogg, Brooks, Kenedy, and northern Hidalgo Counties. Visibilities
are generally 5 to 7 miles, but could be as low as 1 mile,
especially in the Hebbronville area. These areas of fog should
dissipate by 8 AM.
Morning motorists traveling through these areas are urged to
reduce speed, use low beam headlights, and avoid following other
vehicles too closely when encountering fog.</description>
